article.headline: St. Francis, NY 60, Wagner 53
article.story: STATEN ISLAND, N.Y. -- Ricky Cadell scored 22 points and led St. Francis (N.Y.) to a 60-53 victory over Wagner College on Saturday night. Cadell shot 7-for-17 from the field and nailed four 3-pointers for the Terriers (7-9, 4-2 Northeast Conference). Kayode Ayeni chipped in with 12 points. The game was close throughout, and a 3-pointer from Wagner's Chris Martin cut the Terriers' lead to 50-49 with 3:48 remaining. However, the Terriers responded with an 8-0 run, and a layup from Ayeni gave St. Francis a 58-49 lead with 57 seconds left to secure the win. Martin finished with 16 points and six rebounds to lead the Seahawks (2-17, 0-6), who have lost eight straight games. Tyler Murray chipped in with 14 points and five assists. Wagner shot 46.3 percent from the field (19-for-41), but committed 22 turnovers that led to 22 points for the Terriers. The Seahawks were also outscored 10-0 on fast break points.
